caption: Welp. I must say I was pretty disappointed. Last time I was here with my friend the service was slow but at least we got what we ordered. On a Tuesday evening when its not very busy we waited for a while to be served, then we take our order and wait again until I had to pay for another 40 minutes for my car to be parked in the street. We then got our food and it was okay. No complaints on my crab cakes. However when we were done I told the waiter I wanted the make your own smores thing. Instead got fondue for 2😕 . I mean smores and fondue dont even really sound similar so im confused how that mix up could happen. The real kicker though was the food for the fondue. (remember we wanted the smore thing not the fondue thing) You could tell that the food on the dish was pretty old. The strawberries looked like they been in the fridge for more than a week and a half. Not to mention bits of mold on one of them. The pretzels were stale and looked a bit wrinkly? If your pretzels are wrinkly that means its time to switch them out for fresher ones lol. However the brownie was good and the bananas were good also. Unfortunatly the main reason why I wanted to go to the chocolate bar was for the make your own smores because of how different and unique it is. So was it worth the very long wait? (we were there for probably more than a hour and a half with only a few people in the restaurant), no I wouldn't say so. Would I come back? Until i hear that the service is a bit faster. 😕
Edit to add response: oops, my bad. I didn’t realize there’s an expiration date on reviews.

Took a while to get seated; which was understandable we didn't have reservations.  Afterwards service was very slow. We order crab cakes, a burger, and make your own smores.  I was never asked how I wanted my burger, but it came out burnt. My girlfriend's crab cake turned out good though, the waiter then brought out the check but forgot our dessert.  We asked about the dessert and the waiter brought out the wrong dessert; she then apologized and said she had a case of the Monday's (It was Tuesday though)  The dessert she brought out was more expensive then what we ordered, and had stale pretzels, stale vanilla wafers and moldy/old strawberries.  Never were we asked if everything was going well, we never got a water refill (till I asked about it), and in total it took longer then than an hour after everything was said and done.  Keep in mind we were the last ones there, and it wasn't packed at all. Personally, I think they thought that because we are a young couple that they could get away with poor service.
menu is limited right now BUT drinks are not! everything was delicious. our server (short brown hair and tattoo sleeves) was SO nice and funny. made my birthday great
dessert was okay but service was slow and not very polite... plate, silverware, and glass had old food and other crumbs on them

Looked nice but couldn't tell if it was open or not... update I saw the owner reply so we looked again, glad we did, ordered delicious food especially the cheesecake and ice cream!  Was pretty busy and still didn't take long, the lighting adds to the ambiance for sure so just stop and try it for yourself.
BEST HOT CHOCOLATE I HAVE EVER HAD !!!!!
Fun food options, unique drink menu. Very comfortable seating, but everything was a little too pricey.
It's simply gorgeous
Excellent
Great food, too many chocolate desserts to choose from, and an amazing 80s alternative sound track!  We will be back!!

Ive eaten here several times trying different dishes and most of what Ive had ranges from good to mediocre..nothing amazing...its way overpriced for the portion size and quality. Ive had a few desserts and nothing was anything to write home about. youre better off going to the bakery at a grocery store. however the hot chocolates are delicious! the chocolate straws are a fantastic touch! the carrot cake is NOT good, it was dry and the frosting had a taste like perfume or something- that went in the garbage...not enjoyable at all and a complete waste of $. also when i ordered a burger on door dash, i said not to include the usual chips and aioli, but asked in place of those for some onion straws on the burger. they charged me an extra $1.20 for that. seriously? they couldnt call it even? the photo is a dessert that cost $8!! a skinny little sliver that was just ok. the brownie was bland. not rich and sweet. update** the burgers here used to be one of the best around, seemed fresh and hand made, but the last time i ordered the meat was awful! like it had been frozen for years, the texture was terrible and it looked like pre-formed frozen burgers that tasted nothing like the original burgers from even a year ago. total disappointment that they cut corners on quality to save $.
Horrible service, hair in my good, dirty seats, dirty table, streaky/foggy dishes never returning they prices definitely don't match they service

This place is not all that it seems. The name sounds great and the pictures are intriguing but nope! I guess you don't know unless you try it and we tried it and weren't happy. So much went on its hard to even explain but when we talked to the "new" manager he explained that the pictures we saw online are old and outdated and he wishes the food was as good as 3 years ago! Sorry but never again. Cute idea though!  Also! I feel they need new leadership. Here's a tip mac and cheese should have cheese and be tasty. It was bland and dried out. And if your going to be a "manager" you should act like one and dress like one. He bashed his own staff saying the cook is "new" and he had so many call offs. But hunny it dosen't take much for some mac and cheese and a diet soda. Hilarious!  there wasn't any bubbles in the soda and he says " looks like we ran out".  What a joke if you want good food find a hot dog stand instead trust me!
These were in fact the best crab cakes I have ever had!

The waitress/service was awesome. So were the drinks, but the food wasn't that great. We had specific things we did not want on our sandwiches, but it was on there. I ordered dessert, but didn't finish it and took the rest home. My husband went to have my leftovers and found a piece of cardboard in the dessert. People were also walking around without masks. Unacceptable! Will go back for the drinks, but thats about it! My bill was over $200 for 3 people-we would expect our order to be right and not have inedible things in it. I have reached out to the restaurant and received no answer.

We also tried the chocolate shooters which were good! The food was ok. Sandwiches, burgers and pizzas. The dessert list is extensive. I have gone to the Chocolate Bar for many years. Recently, I went and the menu is completely different. I ordered the chocolate pasta and the sauce was super runny. Previously it was made with homemade pasta not boxed bow tie. It came with corn and a toast this time it has a tiny sprinkle of bacon on top. It didn’t taste like much. I normally get the creme brulee, but they don’t offer that anymore either. A majority of the menu was removed when they reprinted. The appetizers were left off and were significantly reduced. I was really disappointed. I loved how the food was prior to the revamp of the menu and restaurant. Also, it seemed as though they didn’t want us to eat there due to no reservation, however they only had one table of two people that was taken. It was super empty.

Food wasn't too bad, got a pizza but it was mostly cheese, could've been less cheese and more sauce because I didn't taste any sauce, also not fully cut through and didnt give us a knife to cut it but gave us spoons? The server seemed to want as little to do with us as possible, for example when she dropped off the food said, "here's your food" and walked away right away, not even a, "anything else?" First, didn't even ask if we wanted drinks at all, didn't check on us at all..dessert was good though. Not tempted to go back. My husband got a ham and cheese panini with chips on the side and I got a bowtie pasta in a cheese sauce with a little bit of white chocolate in it and bacon. It was heavenly. For drinks, we ordered one swedish fish martini and one rasberry truffle martini. Yum! The drinks are to die for. Out of this world.

Customer service is out of this world (and so are the martinis). I ordered through Grubhub and the first driver that came refused to take my order because it contained alcohol. They called to tell me this, and also told me they gave me a free dessert because I had to wait longer. This wasn’t even their fault, yet they cared enough to make it up to me (It was carrot cake and it rocked). The food was still appropriate temperatures when it came, and we loved everything. The cocktail was amazing and came with the cutest presentation. My to-go bag even had a dollar bill in it with an apology note since they accidentally over-charged for a salad upgrade (that I would have never noticed otherwise). The manager, Bill, was absolutely great and I’m sure he doesn’t get paid enough. If I could give them more than five stars I would.

My boyfriend and I were planning on spending our 4 year anniversary here and made a reservation a week in advanced. We had our reservation Sunday at 7:30pm. Both of us had always heard good things and were excited to go and see for ourselves. We arrived around 7:20pm and told the hostess we were there for our reservation, in which she hesitated and said I will get a table cleared for you. If we had a reservation, why wasn’t a table set up for it? The place was very small and downstairs was already pretty full so we figured we would be placed upstairs. Wrong. Instead we were seated in a small corner near the bathrooms, UNDER A STAIRWELL. The table had an extremely bright light in our faces and it was at least 80 degrees in the restaurant. The menus were ripped up but decided to look through it. We then talked and decided that we would not be staying here for our special night and left. We both are very disappointed and won’t be going back.

Worst experience at a "restaurant." I have been here a multitude of times and the service isn't always great but nothing to post about. I came here for my birthday, waited 45 minutes for our drinks, got our food, friend found a hair in it. We complain, the waitress inspects the food like a detective. Couldnt just say im so sorry and take it. She gets something else, another 20 minutes. We ordered more drinks and dessert. Another 45 minutes for our drinks, got our dessert. Found a hair in my cheesecake, i went downstairs to speak to the manager about this ridiculousness. The manager gets to me, starts by listing off the things we are getting for free and asked "so what else is wrong" so i tell him i found another hair in my dessert. He asks "well where is it?" I tell him at the table so he said "so lets see" and proceeds to walk to my table to inspect it like the detective waitress before him. I asked, why do you need to see it? Do you not believe me? And then proceeded to tell me and my family that the first dish didn't have a hair in it. Couldn't just say he was so sorry, ill take care of you. He and the waitress just were literally challenging us. I've been here so many times, now for my birthday, what do i or we get for having not finished our food and have a terrible time? It was so insane to be treated like that after having been here so many times. That definitely will change.

i enjoy the atmosphere.

Let me begin by saying the Martinis were delicious and desserts were exceptional! However, Service was slow and the waitress was not attentive to our party. One entree had a hair in it! Had a fun chocolate martini before dinner that was super yummy and took advantage of the restaurant week menu.  I had the Salmon and my guest had the filet mignon. We also decided to get an appetizer and went with their fried pierogi's- HIGHLY recommend. You get 5 of them, and they are to die for. We both went for their filet mignon for dinner that came with asparagus and white potatoes. We both requested them to be cooked medium rare, and they came out perfect.
I enjoyed my time here, they have some repair and painting to do to get five stars. Service was fast but there weren't many people here.

I moved to Buffalo 5 weeks ago and have enjoyed every restaurant I've tried so far. When they say Buffalo is known for their food, they weren't lying. Well...until you get to the Chocolate Bar. I guess my first mistake was thinking I'd receive good service at a high end martini bar. The second mistake was thinking they'd care enough to make the experience right. After one of the longest Mondays of my life, all I wanted was a quick bite to eat, so I go into this place, after walking by it daily for the last 5 weeks, and ask if they have food to go. The bartender says "yes," so I order the Mediterranean salad with chicken instead of shrimp. This was ar 8:15. By 8:45 I still didn't have my order so when I asked the bartender how much longer, she told me she'd check. When she comes back, she apologizes and tells me that the cook never informed her the salad was ready and told me not to worry though because she made sure there was chicken on it like I ordered. So while the other bartender is ringing me up, I open the container to double check and find that the chicken is cold! So of course I inquire if this is normal and her exact response was "oh I don't know if its supposed to be cold, I've never had it!" Well um anyone who waits 30 minutes for a salad knows the chicken is supposed to be warm! After walking to my car, I realized I didn't want to pay $12 for a salad I had to wait 30 minutes for that has cold chicken on it so I go back and ask them for a refund. Well don't you know the manager has just stepped out for a coffee run and was the only person with the ability to refund my card. Now I get it, everyone is entitled to a break, but you'd think the bartender would have offered to make me a fresh salad while I waited. NOPE! After 10 minutes the manager returns and refunds my money after giving me some speech about how the cook never told the bartender the food was ready. You would have thought after waiting 45 minutes, she'd offer me to keep the salad since they have to throw it away anyway, but apparently that wasn't even a thought in her mind! What a joke! I'll never be back and will be sure to share my horrible experience.
